sample_extract_protocol_ch1: RNA was extracted from 300K cells using the Zymo Direct-zol miniprep kit (Cat# R2051) and RNA quality assessed using the Agilent DNA tape screen assay. The RNA Integrity Number (RIN) scores for all samples were > 7.0., Total RNA libraries were generated using the NuGEN Ovation® SoLo RNA-Seq Library Preparation Kit
sample_data_processing: FASTQ files were generated from the NovaSeq BCL outputs and quality was assessed with FASTQC, Eukaryotic rRNA sequences were removed using SortMeRNA, and the remaining reads were aligned against the hg19 human reference genome using STAR, Following alignment, the gene count matrix was generated using featureCounts
supplementary_files_format_and_content: tab-delimited text files include raw count values for each sample

sample_data_processing: FASTQ files were generated from the NovaSeq BCL outputs and used as input to the ENCODE ATAC-seq pipeline using the MACS2 peak-caller with all default parameters, Output narrowPeak files and aligned BAM files were used for downstream analysis.
supplementary_files_format_and_content: tab-delimited text files include raw count values for each sample

sample_extract_protocol_ch1: PBMCs were thawed and nuclei were extracted as for ATAC-seq. The single-cell suspensions of scATAC-seq samples were converted to barcoded scATAC-seq libraries using the Chromium Single Cell 5′ Library, Gel Bead and Multiplex Kit, and Chip Kit (10x Genomics)., The Chromium Single Cell 5′ v2 Reagent (10x Genomics, 120237) kit was used to prepare single-cell ATAC libraries according to the manufacturer’s instructions. Quality was assessed using Agilent DNA tape screen assay.
sample_data_processing: Sequencing data were used as input to the 10x Genomics Cell Ranger ATAC pipeline to demultiplex BCL files, generate FASTQs, and generate feature counts for each library., For scRNA-seq and scATAC-seq integration, fragment file outputs generated using CellRanger ATAC count were analyzed using ArchR following the standard workflow and with default parameters unless otherwise specified., Cells with a transcription start site enrichment score < 4, cells with fewer than 1000 detected fragments, and p ...

The single-cell suspensions of scATAC-seq samples were converted to barcoded scATAC-seq libraries using the Chromium Single Cell 5′ Library, Gel Bead and Multiplex Kit, and Chip Kit (10x Genomics)., The Chromium Single Cell 5′ v2 Reagent (10x Genomics, 120237) kit was used to prepare single-cell ATAC libraries according to the manufacturer’s instructions. Quality was assessed using Agilent DNA tape screen assay.
sample_data_processing: Sequencing data were used as input to the 10x Genomics Cell Ranger ATAC pipeline to demultiplex BCL files, generate FASTQs, and generate feature counts for each library., For scRNA-seq and scATAC-seq integration, fragment file outputs generated using CellRanger ATAC count were analyzed using ArchR following the standard workflow and with default parameters unless otherwise specified., Cells with a transcription start site enrichment score < 4, cells with fewer than 1000 detected fragments, and p ...
